args:
Leif and Cecile attempt to flee Grams, but are
thwarted by Harle and taken captive. As Cecile's
condition deteriorates, she plots a jailbreak to
attain more Manachew. The pair soon succeeds
and puts the dungeon behind them.
Don't get too excited—we're still inside\nGrams territory.
But there's a closed checkpoint that we can\nuse to get past the border. Let's hur—
If you don't fancy starting new lives as\nhedgehogs, you'll both come quietly.
Forgive me, Leif. This is my fault.\nMy plan was too easily read.
If either of us is to apologize, it ought to\nbe me for dragging you into this.
Still, how did they know? This checkpoint's\nnever guarded—it isn't even on the maps!
Which is precisely why it was so obvious.\nWhat other exit would you choose?
I was certain you remembered all of our\nOfficers Academy lessons about using the\nlay of the land to one's advantage.
Hello, hello, my old friends! It has been\nquite some time.
I'd wondered where you slunk off to after\nleaving the Empire, Harle. I see you now\nmake your bed with the Northern Church.
Wait! But that means the ambush of\nthe White Sparrows...

Was set in motion by yours truly, yes!
Nothing personal, old friend—removing
your little band simply makes the war on
New Alberia that much easier.
And once that's done, you can move on to\nall of South Grastaea.

Very astute! Though I suppose it's not
much of a mystery, considering we issued
a notice recruiting mercenaries for an
invasion force.
Life truly is an unpredictable thing!
To think the day would come when I would\nplace two of my classmates in chains!\nTell me, how does it feel from your side?
Oh, but I am! Honestly, I can't remember\nthe last time I was quite so tickled.
Two knights who reached the height of\nhonor as royal guards are now sitting in a\ndungeon awaiting their fates? It's farcical!
Now while I would dearly love to stay and\ncatch up, I'm afraid I'm quite busy with the\npreparations for your execution.
Oh, and I know we're enemies, but seeing\nas we share an alma mater, I'll do what I\ncan to ensure it's...mostly painless.
I didn't think it was possible for Harle to\nbe any more twisted, but here we are.
He always had an edge as a cadet, but at\nleast his ideals were noble and he stayed\ntrue to them.
Losing such ideals will change a person.\nBut you're right—he wasn't always this\nway. In fact, the Harle I remember was...
Some years earlier, at a public dining hall\nin the Alberian capital...
I can scarce believe we'll be graduates at\nthis time tomorrow and knighted into the\norder soon after.
We've long dreamed of becoming the\nblades and shields of Alberia, and now\nit is almost reality.
I find it harder to believe it took so long!
Are you mad? You and Cecile are both\ngraduating a year early—you've had a\nshorter path than any of us.
Sadly, we commoners don't have the\nluxury of infinite time.
Then let's hear it, Harle: What sort of\nknight do you intend to become?
Why, one who fights for his ideals,\nof course!

I seek to build a world where a person's
worth isn't set the moment they enter it—
a world where even the lowborn can attain
the loftiest of heights!

The talents of the genius slave afford him
no opportunity, while blue-blooded fools
drive entire nations to ruin. This is no
world I wish to live in.
Spoken like a true knight! It gladdens me\nto hear you would take up your sword for\nthe powerless.
Always happy to impress. But I've shared\nmy answer—let's hear yours.
I strive to become a knight who defends\nthe peace of his homeland.

I had my sights set on joining the royal
knights since I was a boy, that I might
fight for my king and this country I so
dearly love.
Ha! Leave it to the valedictorian to have\nthe perfect answer.
I seek to be the king's sword, of course.
To pledge my unshakable fealty and\nsupport and protect my king no matter\nwhat may come. This is my ideal and my—
GRRR! Stop it, stop it, stop it, stop it!\nI don't want to think about the shining\nperson I used to be...
*pant* *heave* Gotta get my Manachew...\nOh, dammit! Harle confiscated it when he\narrested us, that little weasel!
Well, he was right about one thing:\nLife certainly is unpredictable.
Since we last met, I turned my back on the\norder and Harle cast all honor aside.
How did you do it, Leif? How did you\nmanage to remain a knight despite\neverything that's happened?
I know you felt as much despair as any of\nus when Alberia fell to Dyrenell.
Seeing the king you served transformed?\nThe shame of being powerless to stop it?\nHow did those things not break you?
You stayed a knight, even if it meant\ntaking a new king and serving a new\nkingdom. I just want to know how.
Because I carry my own justice inside me.
＂Knight's Code, Article 10: A knight is a\nconduit for justice and good. Let iniquity\nand evil ever face your blade.＂
That's the last of the ten articles of\nknighthood they taught us at the academy.
It may be the last, but it has ever been\nfirst in my heart.
A knight's last bastion is the justice within\ntheir own heart. So long as that stands,\nthey remain undefeated.
And these days, my justice lies in the\nhands of Prince {player_name}.
This may be the lack of Manachew talking,\nbut that ＂justice＂ word has a way of ringing\nin a gal's head.
Speaking of Manachew, I need some bad.\nTime to bust out of this joint.
Then you have an escape plan?
She's been sick for years, and I fear the\nillness may have finally...
Quiet, you! I'll be the judge of this...\nHuh. She really is gone. Well, this is the\nlast thing I needed today.
Good sir guard, as one of Ilia's faithful,\nyou must permit me to lay her to rest in\nthe proper fashion.
Did you forget the part where you're a\nprisoner? You don't make demands!

Even just loosing her bindings and laying
her flat on the floor would be a mercy, sir.
Please, if you bear any love for the
Goddess, you must do this thing!
This is our way in the south...though\nperhaps the Northern Church teaches that\nthe dead are beneath Her gaze.
Enough! Fine! I'll loosen her ropes if that'll\nget your yap to shut.
Guess I should thank her for saving us the\nhassle of an execution. Maybe you'll do us\nthe same favor and—
Thanks for setting me free, bud.
Were you always the sort to resort to such\nunderhanded ploys?
I had a lot of room to spare after tossing\nout justice and honor, so I picked up a few\ndirty tricks along the way.
Now, let's go. Nothing's getting between\nme and my Manachew!
Heh. And yet somehow, you still remain\nthe same one-woman army...
